BRAZIL: Brazil current account deficit at 2.8 pct of GDP.Brazil current account deficit at 2.8 pct of GDP.Brazil's current account deficit for the first seven months of 1996 stood at 2.8 percent of gross domestic product, versus 3.9 percent in the same period a year ago, a senior Finance Ministry official said.Jose Roberto Mendonca de Barros, economic policy secretary, told reporters the current account deficit in the period January to July this year amounted to $9.554 billion.Following July's $334 million trade deficit, the current account deficit in that month was $2.013 billion.-- Michael Christie, Brasilia Newsroom 55-61-2230358